;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*Fruiting - After letting mycelium fully colonize casing introduce a couple hours of light to the terrarium every day to initiate pinning&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Never allow the mycelium to completely colonize the casing layer.&amp;nbsp; Introduce fresh air exchange at 30% colonization or so.&amp;nbsp; Don't keep in the dark at any time.&amp;nbsp; Give ambient light from day one.&amp;nbsp; Use a bright fluorescent lamp at fruiting time.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*Harvest - As mushrooms begin to appear pick them just after the veil breaks to prevent overlay(I think) - If the casing layer becomes damaged to to harvest patch spots up with 50/50 mix.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The casing layer won't get damaged if you'll slice off the mushrooms at the base with a sharp knife rather than ripping them out, which causes terrible damage.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;he things I did leave out was my terrarium design, nuking substrate to sterilize and things of that sorts&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't get anything associated with mushroom growing anywhere near a filthy microwave.&amp;nbsp; Besides, they neither pasteurize nor sterilize.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14996689</next>\n<prev>14994953</prev>\n<first>14994698</first>\n<last>15009011</last>\n<when>1314618841</when>\n<utime>08/29/11 02:54 PM</utime>\n</post>"}